WHAT IS Autumn Emacs?

Autumn Emacs is a GNU Emacs profile that is intended to be lightweight (portable) and fast. 
This profile is focused on improving the development experience of OCaml, Racket, Rust

HOW TO USE?

git clone https://github.com/muqiuhan/autumn_emacs ~/.emacs.d --depth=1

-------------------------------------------------------

FAQ

1. The problem of the proxy
   This configuration opens the proxy by default, which can be seen in the `Use Proxy` item of settings.el. If you don't need it, you can set it to nil and turn it off manually.

1. The problem of the mirror of source
   For mirror sources in mainland China, you can check the parameters of the `*mirror-source*` item to set